Conversion opportunities?

Add in huge reduction in capex for long-lead projects, very little spare capacity, very few short-term cycle projects, and zero conversion opportunities that make economic sense and you have everything you need to know. It’s called root cause analysis.

A real piece of news that matters. Demand continues to increase (100.9mb/d) and world inventories continue to draw. It’s called a structural deficit. Just don’t understand why so many people lose sight of what really matters.
